race.comment: Currie-trained EXTOL (6) was expected ton win first up and did a good job beaten 1L. He hasn't missed a beat and is well placed to win with the extra fitness. HERBIE TOWN (8) peaks and posted a go0od number 12 days ago in tougher than this. He's likely to sit closer today and on that effort has decent claims. SHEDENZA (10) didn't get into it off a wide gate at Gatton but led just missing here prior. Cartwright will push forward and she's likely to bounce. RAMPANT LION (1) resumes and was around the mark in better company last preparation. As a 2yo he placed twice in Stakes grade, but the form since has fallen short of that. He's obviously had issues but is good enough and the betting will be key.
